description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTENSIVE CARE UNIT (ICU)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6 REGISTERED NURSE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time Permanent Position Available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a full time, enthusiastic, motivated NMC registered Band 6 nurse to work within our Intensive Care Unit team. We are a General Intensive Care Unit with 6 beds. Being a general ICU means that we care for a huge range of patient’s with both surgical and medical needs, all requiring organ support. The variety is appealing to those interested in a wide range of clinical scenarios. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a team of approximately 55 staff from Nurses to Health Care Assistants and teamwork is one of our strongest attributes. We offer regular clinical supervision sessions as we recognise ICU can be an emotional and stressful environment in which to work. The staff wellbeing is extremely important to us. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A desire to learn and a commitment to delivering high standards of care are essential. Previous experience of Critical Care nursing in the NHS is essential. A competency based education programme will be commenced for all staff and this will be thoroughly supported by both mentors and our Clinical Nurse educator, who is based within the unit. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;During our last CQC inspection, we achieved good.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Internal rotation to night duty is essential.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal discussion or further information regarding this vacancy, please contact ICU Sister Becky Craig on 01983 534753. Please feel free to visit the unit at any time to have a look around. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
